<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880418-0039 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Eastman Kodak Co. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> EK MC </CO><TEXT>   Eastman Kodak Co., Rochester, N.Y., said it picked Columbus, Ga., as the site for its alkaline-battery joint venture with Matsushita Electric Group of Japan.    The photographic-products giant said the facility at full production, planned for 1991, will have 400 employees. Ground-breaking is set for May.    The joint company will have initial capitalization of $30 million, and will be 70%-owned by Masushita and 30%-owned by Kodak.    The Matsushita group's Matsushita Battery Industrial Co. makes batteries and markets its products under the National and Panasonic brand names. The joint venture is the company's first battery-manufacturing facility in the U.S. </TEXT></DOC>